    <note>Wang Junyu [22230] Poor in youth, he devoted himself to serving his parents. According to the funerary inscription (mubiao) drafted by Wang Anshi, all four sons jinshi, but only Wujiu earned the degree (zhongdi), which must explain the convention of describing sons as jinshi, who clearly did not appear on any jinshi lists--they studied for the degree, perhaps all earning the juren, but they did not hold the degree when their father died. Wang Anshi, WJ, 90.937. CBD, 1, 291.</note>
